      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OAKIE SMOKESHOW (6) is a progressive gelding who has won all three attempts at this circuit and distance so far this campaign, last time coming from this barrier to get home by 4.7m. That took his record at the mile to four wins and two placings from six attempts. Can continue to work through his grades. COASTAL DRIVE (5) has come from much wider barriers in each of his four starts this time in and has produced some good efforts, highlighted by a nose deafest when resuming. He'll be race fit and is better served by this draw. GOLDEN TRIBE (10) brings good form from Victoria, missing by a head in the rich Running of the Bulls last start and winning three back at Kilmore. Draws out but has won three of four attempts at this distance. RED SAPPHIRE (3) had been building towards a win and it arrived in style last start, coming from the back row to score by 10 metres at Penrith. Draws well so could go on with it. SINABUN (7) only beat one home last start but was ticking along well prior.",
